modules.description: The module offers low-level byte-level access and data interpretation operations on a private read-only bigstring type, enabling extraction of individual bytes, endianness-aware integers, and sub-range manipulations. It supports tasks like checking prefixes, suffixes, and infixes, along with blitting, trimming, and splitting, making it suitable for applications such as network protocol parsing, binary file processing, and data validation.

Provides functions to manage a page-based cache using a map function, enabling efficient read access to block devices. Operates on memory-mapped buffers and page indices, ensuring atomic operations during data loading. Used to optimize sequential access to large files or disk regions without manual page management.

provides low-level byte manipulation and interpretation capabilities, allowing extraction of endianness-aware integers, sub-ranges, and byte-level checks. it operates on a read-only bigstring type, supporting operations like blitting, trimming, and splitting. it enables tasks such as parsing network protocols, processing binary files, and validating data structures. examples include decoding little-endian 32-bit integers from byte sequences and checking for specific byte prefixes.
